    <string name="working_dir_text_you_don_t_have_the_permission_to_write">
    You don\'t have the permission to write to the WorkingDirectory or it doesn\'t exist.\n
    \n
    To save the backup of your pictures and store some temporary files, this application uses a directory
    at the root of the volumes carrying the pictures you want to process.\n
    By default it is named \'ThumbAdder\' (this can be changed in the settings).\n
    For this to work, the directory has to exist and it must be permitted to read &amp; write.
    This can be achieved only if you give the application the permission.
    The button bellow will help you to do this easily.\n
    \n
    Once you click the button some screens will appear and ask you to give access.
    All you have to do is confirm every step.\n
    1. You are asked to confirm the directory name and the folder where it is created
    (keep default value)\n
    2. You give permanent read &amp; write access to the working directory.\n
    \n
    \n
    You only have to confirm every screen.\n
    The required values are already set for you.\n
    \n
    Once permissions are set you are redirected to the main screen, and you can start again.\n</string>

